SIMPLE: partially
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Partially
<hw>Par"tial*ly</hw> <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In part; not
totally; <as>as, <ex>partially</ex> true; the sun <ex>partially</ex>
eclipsed.</as></def> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In a partial manner; with undue bias of mind; with
unjust favor or dislike; <as>as, to judge <ex>partially</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Partibility</ent>⟦br⟧
